race.comment: SOUTHAVEN (5) raced here on his home turf 10 days ago and did a good job when beaten a half a length over this distance. He's just missed first up prior and will be fitter again. Has the inside gate and is capable of taking this out. PRESSZORA (1) made it three wins from four race starts, winning on the same day, and like the above was heavily bet. The 3kg claim is handy, but she has the outside barrier today, and that's the niggle. JAY BEE ELL (11) has been close-up his last four and deserves another win. Has his share of ability and comes back to a sprint briefly freshened. He can't be ruled out. RUN FREDA RUN (10) was well supported and easily accounted for a Maiden field over 1400m here, winning by 2.75L. Harder task ahead this time, but she's improving and can race well again.
